Sentencas: Ruddlesden-Popper layered oxide, La0.25Sr2.75FeNiO7-delta (LSFN) is evaluated as a potential electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Leveraging in-situ formation of Ni-Fe nanoparticles to promote the catalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper based electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The in-situ formation of Ni-Fe alloy nanoparticles on the LSFN surface in reducing atmosphere can be believed to enhance the activity towards hydrogen oxidation reaction.
Titulo: Leveraging in-situ formation of Ni-Fe nanoparticles to promote the catalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper based electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LSFN exhibit maximum conductivity of 221.2 S/cm and 0.206 S/cm in air and hydrogen environment.
Titulo: Leveraging in-situ formation of Ni-Fe nanoparticles to promote the catalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper based electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, LSFN is mixed with GDC powder to form a composite electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFC).
Titulo: Leveraging in-situ formation of Ni-Fe nanoparticles to promote the catalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper based electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results show that with the combination of GDC, the maximum power density of YSZ-based SSOFC enlarges from 232.3 mW cm(-2) to 348.5 mW cm(-2), and related polarization resistance reduces from 0.359 Omega cm(2) to 0.108 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Leveraging in-situ formation of Ni-Fe nanoparticles to promote the catalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper based electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The improved performance is attributed to the enlarged triple-phase boundary with the mixing of GDC.
Titulo: Leveraging in-situ formation of Ni-Fe nanoparticles to promote the catalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper based electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, YSZ-based SSOFC with the LSFN-GDC composite electrode shows a stable performance in intermediate-temperature SSOFCs within 200 h, which indicates that LSFN-GDC composite material is a prospective symmetrical electrode for SSOFC.
Titulo: Leveraging in-situ formation of Ni-Fe nanoparticles to promote the catalytic performance of Ruddlesden-Popper based electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
